# 🌤️ Weather App

A sleek and responsive **Weather Web Application** built using **Node.js**, **Express.js**, and **Handlebars (HBS)**.  
It fetches real-time weather data using the **OpenWeatherMap API** and displays it with dynamic weather icons and themed UI.

---

## 🚀 Demo

> http://localhost:8000/

---

## 🧰 Tech Stack

- **Backend**: Node.js, Express.js
- **Frontend**: HTML, CSS, JavaScript
- **Templating Engine**: Handlebars (HBS)
- **API**: OpenWeatherMap API

---

## 📂 Project Structure

weather-app/
├── public/ # Static files (CSS, JS)
│ ├── css/
│ │ └── styles.css
│ └── js/
│ └── app.js
├── src/
│ └── app.js # Main Express app
├── templates/
│ ├── partials/
│ │ ├── header.hbs
│ │ └── footer.hbs
│ └── views/
│ ├── index.hbs
│ └── 404.hbs
├── utils/
│ └── weatherData.js # API logic
├── config.js # API Keys & Base URL
├── package.json
└── README.md

⚙️ Installation & Running Locally

1️⃣ Clone the Repository

`terminal`
git clone https://github.com/Soumen-Developer/weather-app.git
cd weather-app

2️⃣ Install Dependencies
npm install

3️⃣ Add Your API Key
const constants = {
  openWeatherMap: {
    BASE_URL: "https://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/weather?q=",
    SECRET_KEY: "YOUR_API_KEY_HERE"
  }
};

4️⃣ Start the Server
node src/app.js


🌟 Features
✅ Search weather by city name
✅ Dynamic weather icons (sunny, cloudy, rainy, etc.)
✅ Mobile responsive UI
✅ Custom 404 page
✅ Weather info includes:

Temperature (°C)
Weather condition (e.g., “cloudy”, “rain”)
City name
Date display

